# Avoid CSS Gap Property

Do NOT use CSS `gap` property (including Tailwind `gap-*` classes) unless the user explicitly requests it. The `gap` property is not supported on older browsers (Safari < 14.1, iOS Safari < 14.5).

## Instead of gap, use margins

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Using gap
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4">
  <Item />
  <Item />
</div>

// ✅ GOOD - Using margin with last:mb-0
<div className="flex flex-col">
  <Item className="mb-4 last:mb-0" />
  <Item className="mb-4 last:mb-0" />
</div>

// ✅ GOOD - Using space-y (applies margin between children)
<div className="flex flex-col space-y-4">
  <Item />
  <Item />
</div>
```

## Alternatives

| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| `gap-4` | `space-y-4` (vertical) or `space-x-4` (horizontal) |
| `gap-2` | `mb-2 last:mb-0` on children |
| `gap-[8px]` | `mb-[8px] last:mb-0` on children |

## Exception

Only use `gap` if the user explicitly asks for it or states browser compatibility is not a concern.
